To implement the pairwise treatment for Ehenfest+R dynamics, the Liouville
 equation together with additional relaxations can be written as
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\frac{\partial\widehat{\rho}}{\partial t}=-\frac{i}{\hbar}\left[\widehat{H}^{\mathrm{el}},\widehat{\rho}\right]+\sum_{\substack{fi=\ \\
\left\{ 02,12\right\} 
}
}{\cal L}_{R}^{fi}\widehat{\rho},\label{eq:Liouville+R}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where the +R relaxation rate for 
\begin_inset Formula $i\rightarrow f$
\end_inset

 is given by
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
k_{R}^{fi}\equiv2\kappa_{fi}\left(1-\rho_{ff}\right)\text{Im}\left[\frac{\rho_{fi}}{\left|\rho_{fi}\right|}e^{i\phi}\right]^{2}.\label{eq:k_R}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

Here 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi\in\left(0,2\pi\right)$
\end_inset

 is a phase chosen randomly for each Ehrenfest+R trajectory.
 In practice, we use a pure state representation for the density matrix:
 
\begin_inset Formula $\widehat{\rho}=\left|\psi\right\rangle \left\langle \psi\right|$
\end_inset

 with wavefunction 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|\psi\left(t\right)\right\rangle =c_{0}\left(t\right)\left|0\right\rangle +c_{1}\left(t\right)\left|1\right\rangle +c_{2}\left(t\right)\left|2\right\rangle $
\end_inset

.
 The additional relaxation is defined by a transition operator:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
{\cal T}\left[k_{R}^{fi}\right]:\left(\begin{array}{c}
\vdots\\
c_{i}\\
\vdots\\
c_{f}\\
\vdots
\end{array}\right)\rightarrow\left(\begin{array}{c}
\vdots\\
\frac{c_{i}}{\left|c_{i}\right|}\sqrt{\left|c_{i}\right|^{2}-k_{R}^{fi}\left|c_{i}\right|^{2}dt}\\
\vdots\\
\frac{c_{f}}{\left|c_{f}\right|}\sqrt{\left|c_{f}\right|^{2}+k_{R}^{fi}\left|c_{f}\right|^{2}dt}\\
\vdots
\end{array}\right).
\end{equation}

\end_inset

Finally, the time evolution of subsystem wavefunction can be carried out
 by 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\left|\psi\left(t+dt\right)\right\rangle ={\cal T}\left[k_{R}^{12}\right]{\cal T}\left[k_{R}^{02}\right]e^{-i\widehat{H}^{\mathrm{el}}dt/\hbar}\left|\psi\left(t\right)\right\rangle .\label{eq:propagation-system}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $e^{-i\widehat{H}^{\mathrm{el}}dt/\hbar}$
\end_inset

 is responsible for propagating according to the first term of Eq.
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:Liouville+R"

\end_inset

.
 Note that 
\begin_inset Formula ${\cal T}\left[k_{R}^{12}\right]$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula ${\cal T}\left[k_{R}^{02}\right]$
\end_inset

 commute as long as 
\begin_inset Formula $dt$
\end_inset

 is sufficiently small.
 
