However, without any dissipation involved, the three-level system in the
 presence of the CW field will end up in an asymptotic state, 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|\psi\left(t\rightarrow\infty\right)\right\rangle =\left|1\right\rangle $
\end_inset

, by construction.
 To reach a steady state, we need to take into account vibrational dissipation
 of vibronic states.
 Thus, we introduce a non-radiative relaxation from 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|1\right\rangle $
\end_inset

 to 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|0\right\rangle $
\end_inset

 by a transition operator:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\left|\psi\left(t+dt\right)\right\rangle \rightarrow{\cal T}\left[k_{\mathrm{vib}}^{01}\right]\left|\psi\left(t+dt\right)\right\rangle \label{eq:propagation-system-1}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

to impose a phenomenological dissipation.
 The classical EM field does not rescale accordingly for this non-radiative
 transition.
 Here the vibrational decay rate 
\begin_inset Formula $k_{\mathrm{vib}}^{01}$
